You can implement syntax highlighting using HTML and CSS by wrapping code tokens in specific HTML elements with predefined CSS classes. For example:

html
<pre class="code-block">
  <span class="keyword">function</span> <span class="function">example</span>() {
    <span class="keyword">const</span> <span class="variable">x</span> = <span class="string">"Hello"</span>;
    <span class="keyword">return</span> <span class="variable">x</span>;
  }
</pre>



Then, define CSS classes for each token type (e.g., `.keyword`, `.string`, `.function`):

css
.keyword { color: #d73a49; }
.function { color: #6f42c1; }
.variable { color: #005cc5; }
.string { color: #032f62; }


This approach works in environments like EPUB files where JavaScript is unsupported.
